Overview of adj brittle

The adj brittle has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (2) brittle, brickle, brickly -- (having little elasticity; hence easily cracked or fractured or snapped; "brittle bones"; "glass is brittle"; "`brickle' and `brickly' are dialectal")
